#
#Setup

TEXT(beginproblem());

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

Context("Vector");		# or Complex

#---------------Tolerance------------------#
Context()->flags->set(
tolerance=>.02,
tolType=>'relative');  #relative or absolute

#-------------- Image Scaling---------------#
$imgScale = 0.15;

$height = $imgScale*3108;

$width = $imgScale*3509;
		#aspect ratio

#---- Random variables for this problem --------#
$d1 = random(25, 30, 1);
$d2 = random(8, 10, 1);
$d3 = random(12, 15, 1);
$d4 = random(17, 24, 1);
$d5 = $d3;
$d6 = $d2;

$AB = Vector($d2, -$d3, -$d1);
$AC = Vector(-$d5, -$d6, -$d1);
$AD = Vector(0, $d4, -$d1);

$Fmax = random(1000, 1400, 100);

$F_AB;
$F_AC;
$F_AD;

#---- Formulas to compute answers --------------#
$ABmag = norm($AB);
$ACmag = norm($AC);
$ADmag = norm($AD);

$BCratio = $ABmag / $ACmag * $d5 / $d2;
$CDratio = $ACmag / $ADmag * $d4 / ($d3 ** 2 / $d2 + $d2);
$DBratio = 1 / ($BCratio * $CDratio);

$limittingRope;

if ($BCratio > 1) {
    if ($DBratio > 1) {
        $limittingRope = "AD";
        $F_AD = $Fmax;
        $F_AB = $F_AD / $DBratio;
        $F_AC = $F_AD * $CDratio;
    } else {
        $limittingRope = "AB";
        $F_AB = $Fmax;
        $F_AC = $F_AB / $BCratio;
        $F_AD = $F_AB * $DBratio;
    }
} else {
    if ($CDratio > 1) {
        $limittingRope = "AC";
        $F_AC = $F_max;
        $F_AD = $F_AC / $CDratio;
        $F_AB = $F_AC * $BCratio;
    } else {
        $limittingRope = "AD";
        $F_AD = $Fmax;
        $F_AB = $F_AD / $DBratio;
        $F_AC = $F_AD * $CDratio;
    }
}

#---- Answers to the problem -----------------------#
$ansA = $limittingRope;
$mc = RadioButtons([ "AB", "AC", "AD" ], $ansA);

$ansB = $F_AB;
$ansC = $F_AC;
$ansD = $F_AD;

########################################################
#PGML

BEGIN_PGML

[@ image( "21-S-3-4-RP-02.png", width=>[$width], height=>[$height]) @]*

Three ropes are attached to a tower as shown above. In order for the tower to remain upright, the ropes must exert forces such that there is static equilibrium. If the maximum allowable tension in all ropes is [`F_{max} = [$Fmax] \: \textrm{lbs}`], find the maximum forces exerted by all ropes. Use the values provided below:

[`d_1 = [$d1] \: \textrm{ft}`]

[`d_2 = [$d2] \: \textrm{ft}`]

[`d_3 = [$d3] \: \textrm{ft}`]

[`d_4 = [$d4] \: \textrm{ft}`]

[`d_5 = [$d5] \: \textrm{ft}`]

[`d_6 = [$d6] \: \textrm{ft}`]


Which rope will have the largest tension / will reach its maximum tension?

[@ $mc->buttons() @]*

END_PGML

ANS( $mc->cmp() );

BEGIN_PGML

Find the maximum tensions in the ropes.

[`||\overrightarrow{F_{AB}}|| =`] [__]{"$ansB"} [`\: \textrm{lbs}`]

[`||\overrightarrow{F_{AC}}|| =`] [__]{"$ansC"} [`\: \textrm{lbs}`]

[`||\overrightarrow{F_{AD}}|| =`] [__]{"$ansD"} [`\: \textrm{lbs}`]


END_PGML

